reviewText: After the high octane of the back to back "Tower of Heaven" and "Fighting Festiva,l" "Oracion Seis" takes its time. It introduces the lovable Wendy and her cat friend Carla (or Charlie as the manga says) as they fight one of the dark guilds known as "Oracion Seis." The fighting is more slowly paced than previous arcs and some of the members aren't quite as memorable (looking at you Racer) but the arc is still as thrilling as one could expect from Fairy Tail. So check it out if you have liked previous episodes.
summary: Somewhat more of a mellow arc.
Title: Fairy Tail: Part 5

reviewText: what you get:2 dvds2 blu ray disks: 6 episodes on 1 Blu ray, 4 on the other as well as some extra goodiespersonally this should have been released at the beginning of the year but i digressfist off, to not spoil i will be general in my descriptionFairy tail is back in another action packed season. the first few episodes are fluff, no real point other than some good old fairy tail caused laughs and hysterics.old friends return in this season, as well as new ones, to help out our favorite team of fairy tail  on their quests.for fans of natsu, the bane of flame is back with hunger,a fire in his belly...and motion sickness???the celestial maiden is back, lucy is showing off her fashion sense in a variety of cloths as well as some fan favorites and with the ever popular PLU.for  fans of gray, out favorite ice wizard is back, showing off and being cool,...and stripping....GRAY YOUR CLOTHS!the queen of fairys is back, with blades, new armor, and a hatred of..... columns? titania erza  is here!.all these plus our other fairy tail members are present so dont be sad, be glad and join the fun.ok now onto my review lol, i felt this part 1 went by fast i have re-watched it 3 times already and its still good, but leaves you on a cliff hanger, but part 2 is out in a few weeks, (just hope its price drops).overall i believe fairy tail is one of the best modern animes around, it has things for all ages and brings a lot to the table without being repetitive or stale, and will always have the ability to inspire those who watch it. so my only complaint is that it was to quick to watch, other than that no issues and highly recommend it

reviewText: After waiting for almost a year we finally get more episodes of this entertaining and exciting series watch,this set gives us few comedic episodes before starting the Nirvana story arc which well introduce us to a couple of new characters as well as one we will get to know much more about as well as a few returning characters as well. The animation and soundtrack are great and it's also greatly appreciated that the cast for both the subbed and dubbed are here to keep voicing their characters especially for the English dub(Todd Haberkorn/Natsu,Newton Pittman/Gray,Cherami Leigh/Lucy and Colleen Clinkenbeard/Erza). This set only goes up to episode 60 so we'll have to wait until next month to see the conclusion of the Nirvana story arc but don't let that dissuade you from enjoying this entertaining series.
summary: Finally!! More Fairy Tail For Us To Enjoy
Title: Fairy Tail: Part 5
